Function Reference/convert chars « WordPress Codex
-----------

Converts a number of characters from a string.

Metadata tags \<title\> and \<category\> are removed, \<br\> and \<hr\>
are converted into correct
[XHTML](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/XHTML "wikipedia:XHTML") and
[Unicode](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unicode "wikipedia:Unicode")
characters are converted to the valid range.

Usage
-----

` <?php convert_chars( $content, $deprecated ) ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$content` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) String of characters to be converted.
    Default: *None*

 `$deprecated` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Not used.
    Default: ''

Return Values
-------------

 (string) 
:   Converted string.

